# Usage UI & Pricing Rules

## Pricing policy

**Source-of-truth mandate** — When updating pricing (Go `pricing.go`, JS `PRICING`, `usage.mdc`, tests):

1. Check live provider pricing page before writing code.
2. If different from code: update everywhere (Go map, JS object, tests, this file).
3. If matches code: note "verified — no change", proceed.

Thaura AI: hardcoded `$0.50/$2.00` per MTok. Check `thaura.ai/api-platform` if available; otherwise keep last known value.

| Provider | Pricing page URL |
| ---- | --- |
| DeepSeek | https://api-docs.deepseek.com/quick_start/pricing |
| Kimi K3 | https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k3.md |
| Kimi K2.6 | https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k26.md |
| Thaura AI | https://thaura.ai/api-platform |

**Locations that must stay in sync:**
1. `internal/usage/pricing.go` — Go maps
2. `internal/usageui/static/index.html` — JS `PRICING` object
3. `internal/usage/pricing_test.go` — test expected values
4. `.cursor/rules/usage.mdc` — this file (update `last-verified` date)

`est_usd` uses upstream provider table for real model id (after alias→provider→model). Never price on Cursor comparison rows. Date-stamp tables in code; refresh when platforms change.

### DeepSeek (USD/MTok)

Source: https://api-docs.deepseek.com/quick_start/pricing — verify live before updating.

DeepSeek responses expose `prompt_cache_hit_tokens` / `prompt_cache_miss_tokens` — prefer for estimates.

### Kimi/Moonshot (USD/MTok)

Sources: K3 https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k3.md, K2.6 https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/pricing/chat-k26.md — verify live.

### Thaura AI (USD/MTok)

Input $0.50/MTok, Output $2.00/MTok. No cached-token pricing. Hardcoded; check `thaura.ai/api-platform` if available.

## Usage UI (dashboard)

Runs always-on with gateway at `http://127.0.0.1:4002`. No flag, no standalone command.

| Decision | Choice |
| --- | --- |
| Package | `internal/usageui` — embedded HTTP server + static assets |
| Address | `127.0.0.1:4002` (loopback only, never via tunnel) |
| Persistence | SQLite at `{dataRoot}/usage/usage.db` (shared with gateway) |
| UI stack | Go `embed.FS` + HTML/CSS/vanilla JS — no React/Vue/npm |
| Charts | Chart.js 4.4.7 — vendored in `static/` (offline) |
| API | `/api/summary`, `/api/by-day-model`, `/api/by-day`, `/api/by-model`, `/api/by-provider`, `/api/sessions` |
| Lifecycle | Start/stop with gateway |

### Currency support

USD/EUR/CNY dropdown. Persisted in `localStorage` (`discursive_currency`). Rates proxied via Go backend `/api/exchange-rate` → `api.frankfurter.app`; cached in `localStorage` (`discursive_fx_rates`, 24h TTL). New currencies: add to `<select>` HTML + `fetchExchangeRate` `?to=` param.

### Period selector

`#time-range` dropdown controls Spend-by-Period window + granularity. Selection persisted in `localStorage` (`discursive_usageui_time_range`).

| Value | Label | Window | Buckets |
| --- | ---- | --- | --- |
| `today` | Today | Midnight → now | 1h each |
| `yesterday` | Yesterday | Previous calendar day | 1h each (24) |
| `this-week` | This Week | Mon midnight → Sun midnight (UTC) | 1d each (7, future days empty) |
| `last-week` | Last Week | Previous Mon midnight → Sun midnight (UTC) | 1d each (7) |
| `this-month` | This Month | 1st → last day of month | 1d each (future days empty) |
| `last-month` | Last Month | 1st → last day of previous month | 1d each |
| `1h`–`30d` | Fixed lookback | N hours/days back from now | Auto-bucketed |

**Boundaries:** All `since`/`until` are midnight UTC via `Date.UTC()`/`utcMidnight()` — server `Truncate(bucketDur)` works in UTC. Never use local-time `toISOString()` for month/week boundaries.

**`until` param:** Bounded periods pass `until` to cap server padding. Server loop is `!t.After(floorUntil)`, so `until` must equal **last** day/hour of range. Example: Mon–Sun week → `until=Sunday` (7 buckets), NOT `until=next Monday` (8).

**Future days** (This Week/This Month): Server pads all buckets from `since`→`until`, zero-cost rows for unused models → empty bars.

### Spend comparison badge

Current periods (`today`/`this-week`/`this-month`) show +/-% badge vs same time point in previous period:

- **Today** vs yesterday same time-of-day
- **This Week** vs last week same day/time
- **This Month** vs last month same day/time

CSS: `.cmp-up` (red, spend higher), `.cmp-down` (green, spend lower). Parent `.value-flex` uses `display:flex; align-items:center` for vertical centering.

Comparison `since`/`until` computed by `getPrevPeriodComparison()` → shifts primary period back by one unit, caps elapsed duration at current point. Same bucket granularity as primary query.

### Chart.js external tooltips

Spend-by-Model and Spend-by-Provider use Chart.js `external` tooltip for HTML (provider logos). Injected as `#custom-tooltip`. Inline styles from Chart.js may conflict → use `!important` in CSS.

### Session accounting

- **Event** = one upstream API call (one completion). Logged at DEBUG as `msg=usage`.
- **Agent-task window** = consecutive events until idle (`DefaultIdleTimeout` = 30s, override `DISCURSIVE_USAGE_IDLE`). Logged at INFO as `msg=usage_summary`.
- Pauses >30s mid-agent may split one task → set `DISCURSIVE_USAGE_IDLE=5m` for longer window.
- Session id = gateway process run or explicit CLI session id.
- Persist JSONL under app data (`usage/events.jsonl`).
- Log level: `DISCURSIVE_LOG_LEVEL=debug|info|warn|error` (default `info`). Never log secrets.

