## Symptoms & fixes

### `Usage UI not accessible`

| Symptom                                    | Cause                                | Fix                                                                     |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `http://127.0.0.1:4002` connection refused | Gateway not running or port conflict | Start gateway: `discursive start`; check gateway log for `usage_ui_url` |

### `Chart won't load`

| Symptom                              | Cause                                        | Fix                                                                                                                              |
| ------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Blank chart area or JS console error | Chart.js not served (offline-first — no CDN) | Chart.js is vendored in `static/chart.umd.min.js` and served at `/static/chart.umd.min.js` — verify `embed.FS` includes the file |

### `Cost estimate uses wrong price row`

| Symptom                                      | Cause                                                                    | Fix                                                                                       |
| -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Usage $ doesn't match provider invoice shape | Priced pre-mapping alias, wrong provider table, or Cursor comparison row | Resolve alias→**provider+real model**; pick Moonshot vs DeepSeek table; never Cursor rows |

### `INFO flooded with every API call`

| Symptom                             | Cause                   | Fix                                                         |
| ----------------------------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| One log line per completion at INFO | Per-call logged at Info | Use `LogEvent` at Debug; `usage_summary` at Info after idle |

### `Zero cache-hit tokens despite large prompt — code or upstream?`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| `cache_hit_tokens=0` + `cache_miss_tokens=0` with large `prompt_tokens` — looks like a parsing bug | Upstream genuinely returned no cache data (cold request, prefix change, provider switch) | Debug log at `recordUsage` when all zero: `slog.Debug` if `CacheHitTokens==0 && CacheMissTokens==0 && PromptTokens>1024`. Confirms data path works; new-session zero cache is expected. |

### `CSS !important overrides inline styles`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Inline `style="width:160px"` on `<img>` has no effect; element ignores repeated style edits | CSS `!important` (e.g. `.tt-logo-row img { width: 60px !important; }`) beats inline styles. Browser gives zero warnings. | Search CSS for `!important` on matching selector chain. Remove it or update value. Never assume inline wins when `!important` exists anywhere in cascade. |

### `Browser native tooltip shows raw HTML`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| `title`/`data-tip` with HTML (`<br>`, `<img>`) renders as literal text | Native tooltips are plain-text only — cannot render HTML | Inject positioned `<span>`/`<div>` on hover; remove on mouse leave. Never put HTML in `title`.

### `Frontend fetch to external API blocked by CORS`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| `fetch()` to an external API (e.g. `api.frankfurter.app`) from the Usage UI page fails with a CORS error in the browser console | The Usage UI page is served from `127.0.0.1:4002` by the Go embedding `net/http` server. External APIs typically do not include `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: http://127.0.0.1:4002` in their CORS headers, so the browser blocks the cross-origin request. | Add a Go backend proxy handler (e.g. `/api/exchange-rate`) that does the external HTTP call server-side and returns the data to the frontend. The proxy call is server-to-server, which is not subject to browser CORS. |

### `JS innerHTML replacement wipes static children`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| A `<select>` dropdown appears empty after JS runs, even though `<option>` tags are present in the static HTML | JavaScript code that sets `element.innerHTML = <new string>` replaces the entire content of the element. Any static `<option>` children written in the HTML are lost — they are not part of the JS-built string. | Consistently build all children in JS (not a mix of static HTML + JS innerHTML). Alternatively, use `insertAdjacentHTML` or DOM API methods that append without replacing siblings. |

### `Money symbol function undefined at page load`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Console: `moneySymbol is not defined` during page init | Function referenced in an `innerHTML` assignment before its `<script>` block executes. JS hoisting is per-script-block; HTML-constructed strings from earlier DOM updates run before later `<script>` tags. | Define shared utility functions (currency formatting, etc.) at the top of the `<script>` block, before any code that renders HTML using those functions. Or use template literals evaluated at call time. |

### `Period dropdown empty after HTML reorder`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| After swapping two `<select>` dropdowns in HTML, period dropdown shows no options | `<option>` tags for the period `<select>` were accidentally deleted or moved during the edit. | When reordering HTML elements, verify each `<select>` retains its `<option>` children. Use git diff to confirm no loss. |

### `Chart.js tooltip sizing overridden by CSS`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Chart.js `bodyFont.size` etc. not respected in rendered tooltip | CSS rules on `.chartjs-tooltip` or custom tooltip container override Chart.js internal styles | For `external` tooltip (callback controls DOM): set styles directly on custom element. For built-in: use callbacks; avoid broad CSS on `.chartjs-tooltip *`.

