### `Chart.js tick callback breaks chart`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Chart blank after adding x-axis tick callback | `this.getLabelForValue(v)` in tick callback — `this` not reliably scale; arrow fns capture wrong `this`. Category axis `value` is numeric index, not label. | Capture labels in closure: `const labelsForTicks = labels;` then `labelsForTicks[val]` in callback. |

### `Month/week bucket boundaries drift by timezone`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Chart shows wrong number of days at period boundaries | `new Date(y,m,1).toISOString()` converts local midnight → UTC, giving `2026-06-30T23:00Z` in UTC+1. Server `Truncate(24h)` hits wrong day. | All period boundaries must be UTC: `Date.UTC(y,m,d)` for construction, `getUTCDay/Month/etc()` for week calcs. Helper: `utcMidnight(y,m,d)` → `new Date(Date.UTC(y,m,d)).toISOString()`. |

### `Period tooltip leaks zero-cost models`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Tooltip shows providers/models with $0 spend on that bucket day | Server pads all buckets with $0 entries per model; `bucketMap` has every model in every bucket. | Filter in tooltip: `(bucketMap[label] \|\| []).filter(it => +it.cost > 0)`. |
